<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880908-0029 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Consolidated Natural Gas Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CNG </CO><IN> LNG </IN><TEXT>   Consolidated Natural Gas Co., trying to bolster its gas transmission business, said a unit asked the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission for permission to provide long-term natural gas sales to Virginia Natural Gas Inc. and the city of Richmond, Va.    Consolidated Natural Gas, Pittsburgh, said its CNG Transmission Corp. subsidiary also asked for commission approval to transport and store gas for Hanover Energy Associates and Virginia Electric andamp; Power Co.    Consolidated estimated the cost of extending a gas pipeline and other construction at about $34 million.    Consolidated said it will soon begin supplying gas to the Baltimore/Washington area and recently received regulatory approval to supply five utilities in the New York City/New Jersey area.    Virginia Natural Gas and Virginia Electric andamp; Power are subsidiaries of Dominion Resources Inc., of Richmond.    The city of Richmond operates a municipal gas utility, and Hanover Energy is a Virginia limited partnership that operates cogeneration facilities. </TEXT></DOC>